  "claim_boundary": [
    "PKMAP1 is a bounded one-window page-table and lifecycle proof for the exact current PKELF1 product, not the final PooleOS virtual-memory subsystem.",
    "The candidate root clones the active UEFI PML4 and adds only one private PML4/PDPT/PD/PT path after proving the target PML4 slot is empty.",
    "CR0.WP, CPUID NX, and EFER.NXE are required; LA57 and PCID fail closed in this bounded proof.",
    "Every kernel page uses a 4 KiB supervisor leaf with exact effective permissions, and the entry resolves read-execute and not writable.",
    "The full higher-half alias is read and hashed, but no instruction is executed through it.",
    "Framebuffer translation and cache equality mean the cloned root did not drift from firmware state; they do not qualify a final cache policy.",
    "The original CR3 is restored before interrupts or firmware calls, and all private table pages and kernel pages are released before return.",
    "No final memory map, ExitBootServices, retained PBP1, retained page table, handoff, kernel transfer, target-hardware result, or production claim is made."
  ],
